{"article_id":"47EhIh7eRZvaTLPY","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"President Obama ' s comments Friday","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"that the \" private sector ' s doing fine \"","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"attracted sharp and immediate counterfire from GOP nominee Mitt Romney and fellow Republicans ,","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"who said","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"the remarks showed","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"the president was badly out of touch on the plight of the economy .","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"In his remarks to reporters at the White House Friday morning , Mr. Obama tried to draw a distinction between private sector job growth and continuing cutbacks by cash-strapped state and local governments ,","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"it was public-sector job losses and the refusal by Republicans","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"to back his job-creation plans","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"that were holding the larger U.S. economy back .","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"\" The truth of the matter is , we ' ve created 4.3 million jobs over the last 27 months","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"- over 800,000 just this year alone , \"","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"Mr. Obama said .","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"\" The private sector ' s doing fine .","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"Where we ' re seeing weaknesses in our economy have to do with the state and local governments . \"","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"He suggested","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"GOP lawmakers are resisting his job-creation proposals","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"because they ' re motivated by election-year concerns .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"\" If Republicans want to be helpful ,","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"if they really want to move forward","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"and put people back to work ,","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"what they should be thinking about is how do we help state and local governments","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"and how do we help the construction industry , \"","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"Mr. Obama said .","depth":6},{"id":25,"text":"Within less than an hour , Mr. Romney and top Republicans on Capitol Hill were firing back .","depth":4},{"id":26,"text":"Campaigning in Iowa ,","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"Mr. Romney said","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"Mr. Obama ' s comment was \" an extraordinary miscalculation and misunderstanding . \"","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"\" I think","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"he ' s defining what it means to be detached and out of touch with the American people , \"","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"Mr. Romney said at an event in Council Bluffs , Iowa ,","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"pointing to the 23 million Americans","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"who are unemployed or under-employed .","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"\" For the president of the United States to stand up","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"and say","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"the private sector is doing fine","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"is going to go down in history , \"","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"he added .","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"House GOP leaders also laughed off the president ' s assertion","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"that private industry is improving ,","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"citing in part a disappointing jobs report for May and national unemployment still above 8 percent .","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"\" My question would be to the president :","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"' Are you kidding ? ' \"","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"said House Majority Leader Eric Cantor , Virginia Republican .","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"\" Did you see the job numbers","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"that came out last week ?","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"The private sector is not doing fine . \"","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"Later in the day , Mr. Obama tried to clarify his comment .","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"\" It ' s absolutely clear the economy is not doing fine , \"","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"Mr. Obama said","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"while sitting next to Philippines President Benigno Aquino in the Oval Office .","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"\" That ' s the reason","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"I had a press conference .","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"That ' s why I spent yesterday , the day before yesterday , this past week , this past month and this past year","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"talking about how we can make the economy stronger .","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"The economy is not doing fine .","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"There are too many people out of work .","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"The housing market is still weak ,","depth":14},{"id":59,"text":"too many homes underwater","depth":14},{"id":60,"text":"and that ' s precisely why I asked Congress to start taking some steps","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"that can make a difference .","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"And the question then is what are we going to do about it ? \"","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"The president said","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"\" what I ' m interested in hearing from Congress and Mr. Romney is what steps are they willing to take right now","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"that are going to make an actual difference .","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"And so far what we ' ve heard are additional tax cuts","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"that the folks","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"who are doing fine","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"as opposed to taking steps","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"that would actually help deal with the weaknesses in the economy","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"and promote the economic growth","depth":14},{"id":72,"text":"that we ' d all like to see . \"","depth":14},{"id":73,"text":"House Republicans also pushed back at Mr. Obama ' s criticism of lawmakers","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"for not acting on his jobs initiative ,","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"saying","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"it was Mr. Obama ' s \" failed stimulus policies \"","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"that had dragged the economy down .","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"\" Frankly I ' d ask the president to stop engaging in the blame game , \"","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"said Mr. Cantor ,","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"who vowed","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"that House Republicans will spend the summer","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"\" directly focused on how we can make the environment better","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"for small-business men and women to grow","depth":12},{"id":84,"text":"and create jobs in this country . \"","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"House Speaker John A. Boehner , Ohio Republican , said","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"next month he will hold a vote","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"to extend current tax rates , a move","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"he says","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"would help create a better environment for job creation .","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"\" With these looming tax hikes and the regulations","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"coming out of Washington ,","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"we have frozen employers in place , \"","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"Mr. Obama opened the press conference ,","depth":5},{"id":95,"text":"which the White House announced about 90 minutes","depth":6},{"id":96,"text":"before it began ,","depth":6},{"id":97,"text":"with a plea","depth":5},{"id":98,"text":"for Congress to approve parts of his $ 447 billion jobs package","depth":6},{"id":99,"text":"that lawmakers have already rejected .","depth":6},{"id":100,"text":"He said","depth":5},{"id":101,"text":"the \" unemployment rate would be lower ,","depth":7},{"id":102,"text":"and our economy would be stronger \" today","depth":7},{"id":103,"text":"if Congress had adopted his proposals last fall .","depth":6},{"id":104,"text":"\" They left most of the jobs plan just sitting there , \"","depth":6},{"id":105,"text":"Mr. Obama said .","depth":6},{"id":106,"text":"\" I urge them to reconsider . \"","depth":5},{"id":107,"text":"But Senate Minority Leader Mitch McConnell , Kentucky Republican , said","depth":5},{"id":108,"text":"the president is fooling only himself with his assessment","depth":6},{"id":109,"text":"that the private sector is \" doing fine. \"","depth":6},{"id":110,"text":"He said","depth":5},{"id":111,"text":"Mr. Obama should work with the GOP on extending George W. Bush-era tax cuts for all Americans","depth":6},{"id":112,"text":"that are due to expire Dec. 31 .","depth":6},{"id":113,"text":"\" Whether the president wants to acknowledge it or not ,","depth":6},{"id":114,"text":"we are now living in the Obama Economy ,","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"and no ' Post-It Note ' proposal can reverse the damage","depth":8},{"id":116,"text":"done by his policies over the past 31⁄2 years , \"","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"Mr. McConnell said in a statement .","depth":5},{"id":118,"text":"\" It ' s baffling that","depth":6},{"id":119,"text":"in the face of all evidence to the contrary , this president still believes","depth":7},{"id":120,"text":"that spending money","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"we don ' t have to inflate the government","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"is the answer to America ' s economic problems .","depth":8},{"id":123,"text":"The Obama Economy is even slower now","depth":7},{"id":124,"text":"than when we extended the rates in 2010 -","depth":7},{"id":125,"text":"raising taxes on job creators in this slow economy is simply not the elixir for his failed policies . \"","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":251,"left":219,"right":250,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":219,"left":131,"right":218,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":131,"left":128,"right":130,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":127,"right":2,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":127,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":130,"left":3,"right":129,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":129,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"attri